edu.ucla.sspace.util
Class PairCounter<T>

java.lang.Object
  edu.ucla.sspace.util.PairCounter<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Counter<Pair<T>>, Serializable, Iterable<Map.Entry<Pair<T>,Integer>>
public class PairCounter<T>
extends Object
implements Counter<Pair<T>>, Serializable

A utility for counting unique instance of pairs of objects. This class provides several overloads for callers to provide the objects themselves without needing to explicitly create a Pair instance.

This class supports iterating over the set of instances being counted as well as the instances and counts together. All collections views that are returned are unmodifiable and will throw an exception if a mutating method is called.

This class is not thread-safe. Unless otherwise noted, all methods will throw a NullPointerException if passed a null element or a Pair with a null element.
